<title>SINGAPORE: Nicholas-Applegate starts Singapore operations.</title>
<headline>Nicholas-Applegate starts Singapore operations.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-08-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Nicholas-Applegate Capital Management  Asia said on Friday it has started its Singapore operations under  its brand name.</p>
<p>A company statement said the name change reflected its recent acquisition  of Credit Lyonnais International Asset Management-Asia (CLIAM-Asia),  the Asian asset management division of French bank Credit Lyonnais  SA.</p>
<p>CLIAM's five funds will now be renamed using the Nicholas-Applegate  brand.</p>
<p>The U.S.-based fund company manages over US$30 billion in assets for  individual and institutional investors.</p>
<p>--Singapore Newsroom (+65 870 3093)</p>
